snippet.textDisplay: I know you’ll never see this but with the time on my hands I decided to write. I heard “Anyone” for the first time while my husband was in the mental hospital having an episode brought on by his schizoaffective disorder. It’s the 5th stay since August. He’s a former heroin addict. We have five beautiful children. The pain I feel when I see him suffer leaves me feeling so helpless. You should know your music has been a gift to us. In good times and bad, during dance parties and hospital visits. You’re a blessing from God. We are listening.

snippet.textDisplay: God always listens and He is ready to answer our prayers. The thing is that He wants our whole heart. We are to have no other “gods” that we are looking to. Not piano, guitar, alcohol, people, or shooting stars. Matt. 6:33 says that when we seek His Kingdom and righteousness first, all that we need will be added to us. Her need and the need of us all is to find our contentment in His love and living for His glory. “Anyone” will never fill her void.

Not piano, guitar, alcohol, people, or shooting stars.  Matt. 6:33 says that when we seek His Kingdom and righteousness first, all that we need will be added to us.
